Ecological remarks. This species is widely distributed but rather uncommon, although notable densities of individuals can concentrate on small areas. We found it associated to steppe-like, partly cultivated, to subdesertlike landscapes (
Fig. 17
), where we exclusively collected it within red flowers of Papaveraceae . Its apparently scattered distribution and the difficulty of sampling are probably strongly influenced by scarcity and unpredictability of blossoms due to poor and irregular precipitations.
